{"word":"ἐπεγείρω","slug":"ἐπεγείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπεγείρω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-εγερῶ</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to awaken, rouse up</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be roused, wake up</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, in forms <el>ἐπέγρετο, ἐπεγρόμενος</el> (which are from an epic <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a> <el>ἐπ-ηγρόμην</el>). <p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to awaken, excite</i>, <b>Solon.</b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>;—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἐπηγέρθη μῆνις</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}